*roboto-2015.03 (07 Mar 2015)

  07 Mar 2015; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> +roboto-2015.03.ebuild,
  -roboto-20111129.ebuild, -roboto-20120823.ebuild, -roboto-20130731.ebuild:
  Re-packaged current state of roboto fonts in googlefontdirectory repo

  03 Mar 2015; Yixun Lan <dlan@gentoo.org> roboto-1.2.ebuild:
  add arm64 support, tested on A53 board

  16 May 2014; Manuel Rüger <mrueg@gentoo.org> roboto-1.2.ebuild:
  Add ~arm keyword.

  11 Nov 2013; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> roboto-1.2.ebuild:
  Mark stable

*roboto-1.2 (06 Nov 2013)

  06 Nov 2013; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> +roboto-1.2.ebuild,
  files/90-roboto-regular.conf:
  Version bump. Adapt to packaging change. Use upstream versioning. I will mark
  this version stable in a few days, and mask the old versions to give users a
  regular upgrade path.

*roboto-20130731 (25 Oct 2013)

  25 Oct 2013; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> +files/90-roboto-regular.conf,
  +roboto-20130731.ebuild:
  Version bump. Add fontconfig file to set Regular weight as default, instead of
  Black. Thanks to John Flatness in bug #464666.

  21 Oct 2013; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> roboto-20120823.ebuild:
  Marked ~x64-macos, bug #486818

  20 Aug 2012; Tomáš Chvátal <scarabeus@gentoo.org> roboto-20111129.ebuild:
  No open bugs. Stable on amd64 and x86. Mark testing on amd64-linux and
  x86-linux.

*roboto-20111129 (25 Jul 2012)

  25 Jul 2012; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +roboto-20111129.ebuild:
  Initial commit. Ebuild by user BT in bug #423727.
